<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 94 / Kimberly-Clark choose UK for European headquarters
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Kimberly-Clark, the US consumer products group, is to locate its European
headquarters in the UK after investigating sites in the Netherlands, France
and Belgium, Andrew Taylor writes.
The company is to consolidate its existing European offices in Paris, the
Hague and in Tonbridge, Kent in one building. It has eight factories in the
UK, two in France, two in Germany and one in the Netherlands.
One of the attractions of the UK is thought to be labour costs, estimated to
be a third of those at continental locations.
Kimberly-Clark has appointed property consultants Grimley J R Eve to find
premises to accommodate more than 500 staff around the south and west of
London between the M23 and A3.
The company will consider building a headquarters on a greenfield site if a
suitable building cannot be found.
It said the UK was attractive because of international schools and access to
international airports at Gatwick and Heathrow.
</TEXT>
