<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 94 / Eagle Trust loses Pounds 13.5m action
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eagle Trust, the film equipment conglomerate, yesterday lost its High Court
action to recover Pounds 13.5m from Swiss Bank Corporation.
The company had claimed that two subsidiaries of the bank, SBCI Savory Milln
and Swiss Bank Corporation Investment Banking, were liable to repay the
money which had been misappropriated by Mr John Ferriday, its former
chairman.
Mrs Justice Arden ruled the subsidiaries had not known or suspected that Mr
Ferriday had used the company's money to pay off his sub-underwriting
commitments following Eagle Trust's failed 1987 rights issue.
