<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 94 / Crown Estate shows Pounds 486m rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The value of the Crown Estate, which manages property on behalf of the
sovereign and is one of Britain's biggest landowners, increased Pounds 486m
in real terms between 1985-94, the National Audit Office reported yesterday.
Capital values, in constant 1993-94 prices, rose from Pounds 1.55bn to
Pounds 2.03bn. Net revenue paid to the exchequer, on the same basis, rose
from Pounds 39m in 1985-86 to Pounds 79m in 1993-94.
