<HEADLINE>
FT  29 JUL 94 / Clarke and George hold meeting
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Kenneth Clarke, the chancellor, held his monthly meeting with Mr Eddie
George, the governor of the Bank of England, following market speculation
that they would agree to increase interest rates.
Most analysts feel, however, that the authorities will leave rates
unchanged. Ms Katy Peters, UK economist at Daiwa Europe, said: 'I don't
think we've seen sufficient evidence to have a change in opinion on interest
rates.'
The minutes of yesterday's meeting will be published in six weeks.
