<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUL 94 / International Company News: BCP setback sours offer for bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER WISE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Banco Portugues Comercial yesterday reported a 9 per cent slide in net
income for the first half of 1994, compared with the same period last year,
to Es8.68bn (Dollars 59m). Pre-tax income rose 2 per cent to Es12.41bn.
The results came a day after BCP announced a Es132bn offer for 40 per cent
of Banco Portugues do Atlantico, Portugal's largest commercial bank. Lisbon
stock market analysts said yesterday they expected BPA to contest the bid.
The bank recorded total assets of Es1,987bn at the close of the first half,
up 16 per cent.
