<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Toyota said its British unit Toyota Motor Manufacturing (UK) had begun
exporting TMUK-made engines to Turkey, Reuter reports from Tokyo.
TMUK will export 2,000 1.6-litre engines this year to Toyota's Turkish
venture Toyotasa in Adapazari for use in Corolla cars. The number will rise
to 10,000 engines in 1995.
Toyotasa will assemble 2,000 Corollas in 1994 and 10,000 1.6-litre Corollas
and 10,000 1.3-litre Corollas in 1995.
Toyotasa is owned 50 per cent by Sabanci Group, 40 per cent by Toyota and 10
per cent by Mitsui.
