FT  28 JUL 94 / International Company News: Donaldson to step down at NYSE
in May
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr William Donaldson is to step down as chairman of the New York Stock
Exchange when his first term ends next May. His decision, which was
expected, revived speculation over the identity of his successor.
The most likely candidate to take over is its current president and chief
operating officer, Mr Richard Grasso.
During his 27 years at the NYSE, the 48-year-old Mr Grasso has built up a
wealth of knowledge of the exchange's inner workings. He is also popular
with the exchange's floor traders and specialists, and industry sources say
it is unlikely the NYSE's board will choose an outsider.
