<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUL 94 / International Company News: Steel group shares tumble
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Bethlehem Steel, one of the best-performing big company stocks in
the US earlier this year, fell about 8 per cent to close at Dollars 20 3/4
yesterday, as the company's second-quarter results failed to match
expectations.
After-tax income of Dollars 26m, or 14 cents a share, marked the fourth
consecutive quarter in which the big steelmaker has been in profit, and
compared with a loss of Dollars 14m, or 27 cents a share, a year ago.
The year-on-year improvement stemmed from 'higher realised steel prices and
increased shipments,' the company said. Sales were 10 per cent higher than a
year before, at Dollars 1.23bn.
For the first six months of the year, net income was Dollars 39m, compared
with a loss of Dollars 54m a year before.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Bethlehem Steel Corp.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
