'I think we can look back with satisfaction on the progress made during the
year,' said Mr John Main, chairman.
Since the year-end, Harmony, which has applied to join the main market, has
bought a portfolio of properties for about Pounds 7m from Mr Bruce Owen, who
became an executive director in May.
It has also a conditional agreement to buy a further portfolio from Mr Owen
for Pounds 2.45m, which will be financed though a mixture of cash and
shares.
Losses per share were 0.46p (5.87p).
