<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUL 94 / Observer: Fete accompli
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
That end of term feeling is obviously getting to the boys in Brussels. More
tables had to be procured yesterday outside the press room to accommodate
extra releases spewing forth from an unusually decisive European Commission
sitting for its last meeting before the summer break.
Hiding among the pile were a few paragraphs to the effect that the
Commission had struck a deal with Arbed, the Luxembourg steel-maker that is
buying into Germany's Klockner Werke, whereby Arbed would close a steel mill
as part of a debt write-off already agreed with Klockner. Only problem was,
the decision had not yet been taken and officials said the statement should
be considered void. A decision was taken some hours later.
</TEXT>
